    <!-- User manual -->
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Manual.Title">User guide</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Manual.Intro">With IP Changer you can save your frequently used IP configurations (presets) and apply them to the selected network adapter with a single click. The app requests administrator rights at startup because changing the IP requires them.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="L.Manual.S1Head">1. Creating and editing a preset</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Manual.S1Body">In the toolbar on the left:
• “＋ New” – create a new preset.
• “Edit” – modify the selected preset.
• “Duplicate” – make a copy of an existing preset.
• “Delete” – remove the selected preset (with confirmation).

In the editor you can enter a static IP address, subnet mask, gateway and DNS, or tick “Obtain IP address automatically (DHCP)”. You can also add notes to any preset.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="L.Manual.S2Head">2. Applying a preset to an adapter</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Manual.S2Body">1. On the right, pick the adapter you want to change from the “Network adapter” drop-down (use “⟳ Refresh” to reload the list).
2. Select the desired preset in the list on the left.
3. Click “Apply preset” and confirm the operation.

The status bar shows the result and the adapter’s current IP address is refreshed.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="L.Manual.S3Head">3. Importing and exporting presets</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Manual.S3Body">• “Export” – save all presets to a JSON file (for backup or moving to another machine).
• “Import” – load presets from a previously exported JSON file (imported presets are added to the existing ones).</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="L.Manual.S4Head">4. Theme and language</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Manual.S4Body">In the header you can switch between dark and light theme, and between Hungarian and English. Your choices are remembered until the next launch.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="L.Manual.S5Head">Good to know</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Manual.S5Body">• Presets are saved automatically to your user AppData folder (the storage path is shown in the bottom-left corner).
• Invalid IP formats are flagged before saving.
• If an operation fails, the status bar and a message box inform you about the error.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="L.Manual.Close">Close</sys:String>

